AGI - NATO must also strengthen its southern front, the one that borders the Mediterranean and the Middle East, while the European Union should finally create a common defence in the hive of the Atlantic Alliance. Sergio Mattarella intervenes at the Conference organized by the Sioi on "The 75 Years of NATO" in the aftermath of the Iranian attack on Israel, invented by the defense of a composite coalition, and again urges a strengthening of allied defense on the south-eastern front increasingly crossroads of instability.
&nbsp;
Italy, the head of the state assures, is at the forefront, according to the principle of solidarity, in the missions that "presidiate the north-eastern flank, within a renewed vitality and strength of attraction of NATO, also witnessed by the recent accession of Finland and Sweden". But "there can be no separation between security of the north flank and security of the southern flank of the Alliance." On the contrary, "it was filled with the deficit of the progressive coming less of attention to the Mediterranean and Middle East: current events are eloquent.
&nbsp;
Alongside Ukraine, the ongoing Gaza war, its reflections in the Red Sea and throughout the Middle East - with the risks of enlargement -, the missile action of Iran, the crisis in the Sahel, draw a wide arc of instability that in the Mediterranean finds its dramatic point of convergence, and call Italy to fulfil a role of stabilization and defense of the principles of international coexistence".
&nbsp;
Moreover, the Italian tactical command of the Aspides mission in the Red Sea "is part of this picture". Also because the crisis of these months has "in common a goal: compressing that multilateral system based on international law, of which NATO is one of the leading axes."
&nbsp;
The head of the state, after two years of debate between opinion-makers, intellectuals and politicians, also states that the Alliance has defensive functions within international rules and "to this vocation the alliance has never failed, in spite of the Russian war rhetoric aimed at attributing them nonexistent aggressive and expansionistic logic".
&nbsp;
But there is also a theme of relationship between the EU and the Anglophone allies, most of which in the year of U.S. electoral campaign and the eve of fundamental summits both for the Union and for the Alliance. Mattarella therefore urges the European Union to "enhancing the level of its commitment, and to do so urgently".
"It is &nbsp; a reflection that today is focused on the creation of a common defence, after attempts without results at the end of the last century," because often the EU was "a viewer of events of which the negative effects were".
&nbsp;
Thus "to endow the European Union with a greater strategic autonomy will allow NATO to be stronger, precisely because of the complementarity between the two Organizations, with the strengthening of one of its pillars, today more fragile. More fragile because the reduced co-ordination and integration produces limited capacity for large financial commitments. To remove this condition would benefit everyone in a world irreversibly marked by the role of great international subjects," the President assures. Who recalled how Luigi Einaudi repeated that "the spectrum of decisions for the countries of the continent was reduced to 'existing united or disappearing'".
&nbsp;
For Italy, membership of NATO is not simply an accessory, in the first post-war period our country has joined you firmly as demonstrated by the "large consonances" between its founding Treaty of the Alliance and the Constitution. And the head of the state also points out that "the participation in NATO was first of all an adherence by the Republic to the values of freedom of the Atlantic Charter and, together, an essential choice of re-entry into international life". "It was the time when he took over the expression 'free world', to which Italy chose to belong. It didn't happen without debate. De Gasperi's opponents were mainly communism and nationalism," recalls the President, for whom the Atlantic choice "contributed to the political identity of the Republic which is still today". &nbsp;

